{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FW5s4wokDTtntXsss2etDj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found the issue. The dashboard is started with `--host=127.0.0.1` so it only listens on localhost:\n\n```\n/home/ray/anaconda3/bin/python /home/ray/anaconda3/lib/python3.8/site-packages/ray/dashboard/dashboard.py --host=127.0.0.1 --port=8265 ...\n```\n\nThis is why the Service port is correctly configured but connections fail - the dashboard is only binding to 127.0.0.1, not 0.0.0.0. The dashboard was started with `--include-dashboard=false` which is puzzling since it IS running... wait no:\nThe ray command explicitly passed `--include-dashboard=false`, yet the dashboard process is still active and listening on 127.0.0.1. That's the real problem - the dashboard shouldn't be running at all with that flag, but it is, and it's only accessible locally. The solution is to modify the Ray head Deployment to use `--dashboard-host=0.0.0.0` in the start command instead of disabling the dashboard entirely. Let me examine the Deployment configuration to see what needs to be changed.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4200,"cache_read_input_tokens":33026,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4200},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5766f108-66d9-49fa-a871-849357a0636d","uuid":"dc7dc646-d83c-4690-a1c8-19f7d51db6d6","request_id":"req_011CcQMMvExuajzkXsdzYd1M"}
