{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LeBL1fJFfoUghsjRhmCSEE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The test returns HTTP 200. Here's what was done:\n\n1. **Root cause:** The `ray start` command had `--include-dashboard=false`, which caused the dashboard to bind to `127.0.0.1` only — unreachable from other pods even with the Service port open.\n\n2. **Deployment patch:** Replaced `--include-dashboard=false` with `--dashboard-host=0.0.0.0`, so Ray binds the dashboard to all interfaces, and added `containerPort: 8265` to the container spec.\n\n3. **Service patch** (done first): Added the `dashboard` port (8265→8265) to `ray-head`.\n\nAfter the rollout, `curl http://ray-head:8265/api/cluster_status` from inside the cluster returns 200."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":128,"cache_read_input_tokens":39792,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":128},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5766f108-66d9-49fa-a871-849357a0636d","uuid":"0f744020-d342-4bd0-82c9-3c390d427e42","request_id":"req_011CcQMPzCQBrZZhzbh4Ezff"}
